The Absa Premiership match between is scheduled for Wednesday, April 25, which will now be played behind closed doors in terms of a sanction handed down by the Premier Soccer League (PSL) Disciplinary Committee. "The Disciplinary Committee has sanctioned Orlando Pirates by ordering that the club must play two home matches in a closed stadium. The implementation of one of these matches has been suspended for a period 24 months," read the statement released by the PSL. Disgruntled Buccaneers fans invaded the field and stopped play as Sundowns thrashed the the Soweto giants 6-0 at Loftus Versfeld last year February. Fans who have already bought tickets for next weeks match will be advised in the near future as to how to get a refund. --News24--